  "texts": [
    "Similarly, 1,000 non-duplicated random examples were selected from the Arizona external validation dataset.",
    "For basic dataset statistics, the token length was calculated based on the natural language processing toolkit (NLTK) tokenizer 30, and the lexical variance was defined as the ratio of the number of unique tokens to the number of total tokens in each example 13.",
    "Due to patient privacy policy regulations, proprietary LLMs such as GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 were not considered in this work because versions of those models that were safe for protected health information",
    "were not yet available.",
    "Among open-source models, we selected representative auto-regressive models including Llama-2-7b-chat 27, Zephyr-7b 28, and Med-Alpaca 31 models considering their performance and max input context length on general natural language processing (NLP) tasks and radiology report summarization 13."
  ],
